officialTitle: Timing of Human Chorionic Gonadotropin Administration in Intrauterine Insemination Cycles
inclusionCriteria:
* Mild male factor infertility or unexplained infertility.
* Must be FEMALE
* Must have minimum age of 20 Years
* Must have maximum age of 35 Years
exclusionCriteria:
* Advanced male factor infertility.
* Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) as defined by the Rotterdam criteria.
* Endometriosis.
* Tubal disease.
* Uterine abnormalities or myoma.
* Previous uterine surgery.
* Metabolic or hormonal abnormalities.
